OL,3,CCulture Secretary: Racism experienced
OL,4,Cby Jess Carter is 'horrifying'
OL,6,FConservative leader Kemi Badenoch also
OL,7,Fpraised Carter for speaking out, but
OL,8,Fadded that the UK is "not a racist
OL,9,Fcountry".
OL,11,F"It's heartbreaking to hear Jess say
OL,12,Fthat, as a black women myself, I know
OL,13,Fwhat she's talking about," she said.
OL,15,F"But I would start of by saying, this
OL,16,Fis not a racist country.
OL,18,F"We live in one of the most fair and
OL,19,Fleast prejudiced countries on earth,
OL,20,Fif not the most.
OL,1,W~s1{$~k4{$k7                    G7/10
